article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay 89, Central Michigan 71
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Ryan Evanochko had 25 points to help Wisconsin-Green Bay beat Central Michigan 89-71 Saturday night. Evanochko and Troy Cotton scored 14 points apiece in the first half as the Phoenix hit 16 of 27 field goal attempts on its way to taking a 48-26 edge at the break. Cotton ended up with 19 points. The Chippewas' Giordan Watson rebounded from shooting 1-of-8 in the first half to finish with a game-high 28 points before fouling out. Watson hit seven 3-pointers. Central Michigan (3-5) got as close as 11 in the second half, but the Phoenix (3-5) pushed the lead to as high as 27 thanks to hitting 25 of 31 from the free throw line after halftime. Wis.-Green Bay shot 45 total free throws to the Chippewas' 21. Wis.-Green Bay finished the game shooting 54.5 percent from the field -- 24 of 44. Ryan Werch scored 12 points on 12 of 12 free throws and Mike Schachtner added 10 points and six rebounds. Chris Kellermann scored 18 points and hit four 3s, while Marko Spica added 12 points and eight rebounds off the bench.
